      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Leafs' faithful are staring down the barrel of another gut-wrenching spring, their playoff dreams long since cremated in a bonfire of blown leads and bitter defeats. <strong>Last night's 1-3 thud in Ottawa</strong> &mdash; the regular-season finale against a Senators squad tuning up for the real dance &mdash; capped a 32-36-14 nightmare, eighth in the Atlantic and 35 games back, mired in a seven-game skid that feels like an autopsy on a corpse. They squandered a 3-0 edge Monday versus Dallas, coughed up a two-goal third-period lead, and now it's all over but the packing of sticks; eliminated weeks ago, they're lottery bait, clinging to 78 points and a 15th seed in the draft pecking order. William Nylander's lone tally in Ottawa was a flicker in the dark, but the power play sputtered, the defense leaked oil, and goaltending turned sieve &mdash; this group's core looks gassed, questioning if the emperor has any clothes left. The urgency that fueled 82 games? Vanished. <strong>Now comes the real reckoning: draft lottery odds sharpen if they slot bottom-five, and a summer of hard choices awaits Shanahan's war room</strong>. Toronto sports another lost season &mdash; will they finally rebuild, or just retool the excuses?",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
