    "raptors": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Raptors",
      "league": "NBA",
      "record": "46-36",
      "detail": "3rd in Atlantic Division",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Raptors",
        "body": "The Raptors' playoff pulse thunders on, Scottie Barnes shrugging off the noise with that ice-water glare &mdash; \"That shit don't matter,\" he barked after yesterday's practice, eyes locked on the Cleveland Cavaliers who stand between Toronto and deeper glory. <strong>The series sits knotted at 1-1</strong>, the Raptors' 46-36 grit &mdash; good for 3rd in the Atlantic and the no. 5 seed &mdash; fueling a W1 streak into this cauldron, just 5.0 points out of the divisional pack though 14 games back in the bigger chase. Barnes, the lanky heartbeat at 6'7\", erupted for 28 in Game 2's steal-it-back win, his chase-down blocks turning Scotiabank Arena into a madhouse while the bench torched Cleveland's second unit. What went right? Defense that suffocated Donovan Mitchell late. Wrong? Rebounding boards left dangling like bad passes. This is the crescendo, the 82-game grind distilled to do-or-die. <strong>Game 3 tips tonight in Toronto</strong> &mdash; watch Barnes hunt mismatches, because if he owns the paint, the Cavs crumble and the Raptors roar into Round 2.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
