      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The clock ticks down to Pittsburgh&mdash;eight days until the 2026 NFL Draft kicks off&mdash;with Washington clinging to the No. 7 pick after a grim 5-12 slog that landed them third in the NFC East, nine games back and staring at a <strong>14th overall playoff seed phantom</strong>. GM Adam Peters hosted top-30 prospects at Top Golf in Ashburn Tuesday night, the final pre-draft flurry before Wednesday's cutoff, with Ohio State safety Caleb Downs drawing the hottest buzz this week as his \"floor\" landing spot per insiders. Needs scream loudest at receiver to pair with Terry McLaurin&mdash;they've eyed Carnell Tate, Makai Lemon, Omar Cooper Jr.&mdash;plus secondary, center, and maybe a Jeremiyah Love running back steal if odds hold, though Peters preaches impact over positional dogma, eyeing even linebackers like Sonny Styles. Free agency? Barely touched those holes, and with just six picks (7, 71, 147, 187, 209, 223) after shipping Round 2 and 4 to Houston for Laremy Tunsil last spring, trade-down whispers grow if Love tempts a suitor. Dan Quinn's crew can't whiff like the 5-12 echo chamber. <strong>Watch No. 7 closely April 23&mdash;does Peters pounce on Downs, wheel for WRs, or flip the script?</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
